 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Job Title: VP Technical Architecture Deloitte 10,220 reviews Birmingham, AL 35203 Full-time Deloitte 10,220 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Deloitte is growing its AI footprint and seeking to disrupt the customer service space by creating a solution that anticipates delivery of uniform, compelling, empathetic service experiences across machine, human, and mixed (human + machine) environments. 
 
The Deloitte Service Modernization team is seeking a hands-on VP, Technical Architecture to lead, create and build a tangible AI solution framework and architecture. This position is key to the delivery of technical solution architecture for successful outcome and developing the technical vision and design specifications in a hands-on leadership capacity. 
 
You will bring your expertise of tools and technologies within the AI industry, as well as constantly having your finger on the pulse and remaining current with rapidly evolving trends. Utilizing your knowledge of tools and technologies, you will lead projects with a hands-on approach focused on highest quality of delivery possible and collaborate across teams to ensure successful solution delivery. This role calls for excellent analytical, project management, problem-solving and communication skills to convey your message to team members and other stakeholders.
 
 
 What you'll do 
 
 Lead and mentor a team of technical architects and maintain responsibility for overall technology components
 Build a solution architecture and solution framework working with the Functional Architect to create an optimized solution
 Perform analysis of external components from third party companies for their fitment and integration into the overall solution landscape
 Conduct analysis of Cloud components for designing the solution in a cost-effective way utilizing tools from Cloud when required
 Create a framework working with Principal Data Architect for data flow
 Work in close collaboration with Principal Data Scientist for AI/ML requirements 
 
 Experience
 
 15+ years of experience in an Architect role, with demonstrated deep expertise in building and designing large-scale applications that involve analytics, data analysis systems and AI/ML solutions 
 Strong leadership capabilities with experience in collaborating and leading large teams and mentoring and engaging the team 
 A Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Informatics, Information Systems or another quantitative field is required. A Master's degree and PhD is a strong plus
 Proficiency in the following: 
o Programming languages, like Python, C/C++, Java, 
o Cloud components, like Azure, OCI, 
o Database technologies, especially SQL/NoSQL, as well as PostGress, Cassandra, Bigtable and Cosmos DB 
o Data pipeline and workflow management tools: Azkaban, Luigi, Airflow, etc. 
o Hadoop-based analytic components, such as HBase, Hive, Pig, MapReduce 
o Open-source big data components such as Spark, Kafka, etc.
 Experience in working with operating systems, especially Linux and knowledge of Stream-processing systems: Storm, Spark-Streaming, etc.
 Hands on experience to create and test various POC/POT is a must
 Knowledge of business domains Retail, Banking, and Healthcare is a plus
